                <h1>Exploring the Shadows: The Allure of Film Noir</h1>
                <p>Film noir is a cinematic style that emerged in the 1940s, characterized by its dark themes, moral ambiguity, and stylistic elements like low-key lighting and unusual camera angles. It often explores the complexities of crime, with protagonists caught in a web of deceit and corruption, reflecting post-war disillusionment and urban realism.</p>
